I came for a dinner party. The drinks were watered down, the food was bland, yet over seasoned. The food was also overpriced. I like the scenery and ambience of the restaurant, the manager was nice, but the waiter was rude.

The absolute best thai food in DC. Always very prompt service and polite staff. Will always come here to eat out in Dupont. The pad see ew is my go too off of the menu and I have never been disappointed. Large portions sizes and very flavorful dishes!
Was viewed with suspicious eyes.  Was there with my 20 yr old daughter.  Visiting from NY, we pulled up on LIME SCOOTERS. Food was ok.

I've had problems in the past with Thai restaurants not adhering to instructions surrounding peanuts. As someone with a deadly allergy, this is highly problematic. Mai Thai has always been very accommodating to my allergy, and their food has always been excellent. If you have a peanut allergy, you can absolutely trust this restaurant.

A cool vibe inside with kind workers. The Chicken Panaang Curry I ordered was tasty, but I was very confused as to why they use peanuts in their curry sauce while it is advertised as just Panaang Curry. I have never seen yellow curry with peanuts in it. That’s not the dish that I am used to getting at various places. My Thai friend was also very confused, so I wouldn’t expect to get authentic Thai food here. She was disappointed in the mango sticky rice dessert. Tasty, yes. Large portions, yes. Authentic?

I go with my wife to this place from time to time! This is my favorite place to dine.  I go there many times. The cooking is just great, the crew is polite and the prices are decent. I enjoy being in this restaurant to have a nice meal.
This place always delivers. They have excellent food for reasonable prices, there is no waiting time even when the spot is busy.

I don't think you can go wrong with this joint. Generous serving size for the price, and tastes really good, for the most part. The reason why I'm giving 4 stars is there are things on the menu that can be hit-or-miss. I've generally liked most of them, but their salad was way too salty and the duck that went on top of the salad was way too chewy. I'd stick to their stir fried noodles and/or curry.
Good peanut tofu curry and virgin mojito. Warning: many of their "vegetarian" entrees include fish sauce so be sure to ask!

Mai Thai is a great spot just off the main strip in Georgetown. I ordered a thirty roll deal that came with a miso soup, which I split with one other person who ordered one additional miso soup. All said and done, the total came out to under $40, and we were more than full. The service is quick, and the ambiance is nice.
Fantastic food, great prices.
Never disappointed me, always great food and drinks!

This joint has the best Thai dishes in the DMV.  Well worth the trip to there location on 9th street, n.w.  I wish I lived closer but then again, I'm glad I dont live closer....that's how good they are!!  Thanks guys....keep making that Basil Fried rice w/beef with love

Good service,  good price.   No spice.   I ordered panang curry (my favorite). It tasted bland and more like a mild peanut sauce.  It was good,  but I prefer more flavor. This may be bc of the area...but I'm used to spicey thai food.

I was walking around to find a place to eat and saw this place so I decided to give this place a try. Food are all good, customer service was nice, the only thing that I do not like about the customer service is that, we were just sitting down and had not have any chance to look at the menu, the lady came right out and asked us if we want something to drink right away. We tried the drunken noodle with beef, it was a good choice. You can always ask them for their spices tray, they will bring the spices tray to you if you like it a bit more spicy. The papaya salad was okay, it was not as good as I expected. It did not have tiny crab as the thai papaya salad I used to have. The Mai Thai cocktail was good also. The glass is quite interesting. I will give this a second try when I am around the area.
Good food, nice service!!
I didn't like Pad Thai.  It was flavorless.  The string rolls were good though.

I had the most disgusting experience with the server named Nan here. I went with a group of friends and at the end of the night I had some food left that I was looking to take home. The servers cleared our plates and once the rest of my group got their food back, I noticed I hadn't yet. I asked Nan for an update; I saw her, with my own eyes, look through tub of stacked plates that needed to be cleaned, grab my plate with the food still in it, put food in a box and hand it to me. She literally went through the trash and handed it back to me! I've spoken about this with the manager William, not sure if she's been fired yet! Definitely ruined my view of the establishment.
Good happy hour specials--$5 cocktails.
Great thai food

Great view on the water, and lots of servers - but the food was disappointing. Grilled fish was so old tasting, probably frozen, no flavor. Broccoli it came with was half blanched. when we were seated, 2 of the 4 plates were dirty (dried food still visible). Sticky tables, I was afraid to put my elbows on them. Fried rice was a huge portion, but mostly rice and a few pieces of chicken on top - hardly any vegetables other than a few carrots on top. Garlic eggplant was chopped so tiny pieces, felt like it was made for baby food. Visiting in town from SF, I guess I'm spoiled by the quality of authentic Thai options we have.

Not the best thai food. I ordered fried rice with vegetables and beef and it was OK, not very tasty. I had lemonade and there are no refills. The place, in special the restrooms, was not very clean. Understaffed so the waitress came to our table 7-10 min after we sat. She was polite, though. It was a hot day today and their cooling system was not working well as it was warm inside. Yes, true, the receptionist doesn't even look at you when you leave
Tasty Thai food with reasonably priced meals and generous portions. I had Chicken curry in red sauce over white rice and a Thai tea for drink. I would recommend this place and I would go back again.
Always in yummy restaurant food n dinein category but now they have increased their dishes cost so its a bit more expensive (almost $3-4 per dish)
The food is excellent!

One of the only few places I will go to for Thai food in DC. What's great about this place is that whether you dine in or order takeout, they are consistent. As an appetizer their papaya salad is a great choice. It's a fresh, crunchy, little spicy veggie dish that has a lot of flavor. If you don't like spicy food, their ladna is a great choice and is one of my favorites. The broth is so flavorful that Id rather use a spoon than a fork as my main utensil. The portions are great and you'll catch yourself scraping the plate (as I do each time). When I'm craving something spicy, their drunken noodles hits the spot. They add just the right amount of spice (although you can always adjust that), veggies and noodles and is also packed with flavor.

Great Thai food on Dupont Circle. They have beautiful themed dining areas and a nice patio out front. Stopped by for Happy Hour drinks and stayed for dinner. The food was fresh with great sauce. Would definitely go again. Enjoyed the drinks too.

This was my favorite restaurant until I  came to order food on Sunday which clearly states 1:30pm on the door  and the website is also miss leading it states it's open  at 11:30 when no one was there..What bummer Bad  Management...Good food when it's open...definitely call before you go even if it states its open...

It’s only because of the proximity me to the city where I had an interview that went to eat there and I am not impressed at all with their pad thais and other Thai foods. Though to be fair the ambience is warm and inviting.

Experience was great! Got the spicy crispy shrimp, was a bit spicy, but could've done with a bit more. Spicy scale is conservative for that food. They didn't allow for any changing of the entree, but food was delicious! Fair price in a chill atmosphere.
Food was so so, beef fish was bland and tough.  Waiters could have been more attentive.

Visiting DC to celebrate a birthday. We chose this restaurant based on decent reviews and its proximity to our hotel. Two of us arrived early and got a table, while the others arrived a few minutes later and stood at the door completely ignored by the staff. Once we were all seated, after 10 minutes, we had to wave our arms to get a waitress to come by the table. Our server was completely indifferent to us and borderline rude. Her attitude never improved and, somehow, in a restaurant that was maybe 25% full, we felt like we were a bother. We had appetizers and entrees and everything was (surprisingly, at this point) very good. When we left, the hostess sitting by the door didn't even look up. The food was good, but not good enough to compensate for the lousy service.
We always enjoy this place when the urge strikes to eat Thai. Great menu and the food is always tasty.

Good happy hour specials. The fried tofu was very good. However, it took a full thirty minutes and three requests to get a copy of my bill. During this time, the waitresses alternately spent time standing at the front door chatting with each other, or sitting in an empty part of the dining room chatting together. I asked a lady that appeared to be a manager for my check, but she showed no interest in either getting it for me or asking someone else to get it for me. Nor did I ever receive any kind of apology for the length of time it took.

We shared the specials as we weren't very hungry. These were the shrimp wraps with sweet and sour sauce and the roast duck curry. Both great. Service also good. Would go again but we are only visiting Washington for a few days.
Great food and service...

The food here was just okay. The perk is, that unlike most Thai restaurants, this place has a solid upscale feel, appropriate for semi formal gatherings with friends, maybe even an informal birthday dinner, or to meet somebody for business.  That said, there is nothing impressive about the food, and it doesn't quite compare to something that you might find at a smaller, more mom and pop place that focuses on food more than atmosphere.  Prices are also considerably higher the most Thai restaurants.  What does hold true here, is it the service is just garbage. You have to hunt your servers down for refills and spice trays, and surprisingly, this is one of the few places that you really have to work to find somebody to give your money to when you're done.  We literally ran late and missed an event because we couldn't find our server to get a check. After 25 minutes of frustration we walked into the back to find our servers having their own meal and relaxing. 😠😠😠😠😠😠😠😠😠😠😠😠😠😠😠

You can sit outside (weather permitting) or towards the front where it is busier or in the stalls at the back where it's a lot quieter and the setting cozy.

Good food and good for groups. Place is unassuming from the outside, but extends really far back into the building and has lots of seating. Today Thai cuisine for the area (drunken noodles, curries, papaya salad, pad thai, larb gai, etc.) and all of good quality across the board. Service was pleasant and prompt, even during a busy lunch hour. All in all a good experience.
The portion is very big. I ordered a veg pad thai. It was good but so large that I could only ate one half of the dish. I took home the left over and it was very good the next day.

I eat a lot of Thai food and while I have only visited this location once but I was very pleased!  Overall I enjoyed my meal, service was outstanding, and I recommend the Green Curry.  I saw a reviewer say that the price was a little and portions were a little on the small size. I disagree with this statement. The price was reasonable and the portions are as expected when compared to other Thai restaurants that I have eaten at (which is quite a lot).  Our table had the Pad Thai, Green Curry, Crab Rangoon, and Spring Rolls. I had the Green Curry, Crab Rangoon, and Spring Rolls.  I highly recommend the Green Curry. Lots to eat and the flavors are outstanding. The Crab Rangoon and Spring Rolls were both very good. The same dipping sauce came with both and was okay. I prefer the sweet chilli dipping sauce like others but it did the job!  I would recommend this location.
Good food. Good service.
Really nice atmosphere and decor. Really polite and caring staff. Good food.

I ordered a pepper steak with white steamed rice and tom yum soup there. The food was great but my stomach didn't agree with what I consumed. As the day progressed my stomach was in so much pain, later on during the late evening hours I started puking (throwing up). The sever was okay. Nothing special about the service. I thought this place would be one of my hot spot fav places to eat....not anymore. In fact I'm never coming inside this restaurant again.
Spacious place, good food. Like going here during lunch time, they are fast and quality is good.
Absolutely delicious. Nice atmosphere and friendly staff. Good prices too!
Great food and great drink selection!
Best Asian food I can find within walking distance from office.  Quick and good service.  Really like this place.
Had flamed watercress, it was very difficult to chew.
I'm a huge fan of Thai food and this place is good. I've tried several different dishes from the menu and never been disappointed. Service is very efficient.
Great food and great service! Mai Thai is one of the better Thai restaurants in DC. There is a decent amount of vegetarian options as well.
Food is pretty good. Service wasn't great and the waitress took forever to bring our checks. Good for lunch on a weekday if you are around.
Love the Penang Curry and Papaya Salad!

The manager instead of offering to fix or replace the dish started boasting how popular their restaurant and how great their cooking process was. They had to pay for the food they didn't eat.
Food is fresh and good.  Highly recommend this place
Great for lunch or dinner at a reasonable price. Can get crowded at lunch but its a big space with lots of tables so you can almost always get seated

Worst service ever. I ordered two small food for delivery. I had waited one and a half hour, but the order was never delivered. When I called and asked what happened, they only repeated that they had no fault because I didn't answer their call on the food arrival. The fact is that I didn't have any calls from them. Worst Service I have ever experienced. I had came here for lunch with my coworkers and we received the worst service from our Server named SARAH who ran after us to harass us about why we didn't leave her a bigger tip. What in the WORLD!! Issues I had with her service are as follow: (1) We were placed at the back of the restaurant which was ridiculously hot! It is 102 degrees outside right now and it feels a lot cooler then inside this place. I asked if she could move us to the front because it was a lot more cooler and I was hot and was feeling light heated, she said directly NO there's a fan (3) The fan did NOT work! She did not adjust it or even come back to check if she could fix the fan, she didn't even check if we wanted some water or if our meal was to our liking. Honestly the whole time I felt like it was a Sauna and I was almost at the point of passing out (4) when we received our meals, one of my coworkers was unhappy with the taste of the meal and did not eat it. We ask politely if we could take it off the bill. Sarah was difficult and refuse to take it off the bill. (5) when she finally brought our check and we paid and left. SHE RAN OUT OF THE RESTAURANT AFTER US complaining why we didn't PAY HER MORE TIP!!?? Seriously!! She was not leaving my coworkers and I alone until she got what she wanted. The service was so BAD and you could literally have a heat stroke in there. I am sorry but that is COMPLETELY UNACCEPTABLE!!

The interior is decorated very well. The food is very good. Staff is friendly. The Drunken Noodles are tasty and spicy. Chicken Pad Thai is one of my favorites and they do it well. Portions are smaller than what I'm used to but to me that is not a bad thing. The price is a bit higher though so the portion/price might disappoint some. My only problem with the establishment is their apparent reluctance to use air conditioning. I've eaten here mostly during the day and in the summer it can be quite hot inside.

Decent restaurant with decent choices. Nothing really special about the menu as it just seems like every other Thai place. It was super hot inside the establishment during our time there , to the point were their management had dozens of small fans set up all over the place. The food did take an exaggerated amount of time to get to us for a place that was half empty.
One of my favorite go-tos in the city.
Good food

Service was good, food ok.  Expected bigger (or more) shrimp on the Seafood Paradise entree.  Others in our party liked their meals, Pad Se Ew and Spicy Ginger Chicken, as well as the desert Black sticky rice with pumpkin custurd.

The food was perfect and the host was efficient. The drinks were acceptable but nothing to be overly excited about.  We visited during the recent cold spell and the restaurant felt as if the heat was not working. There were a couple of space heaters but they didn't seem to provide much warmth. All of the guests were seated on one side of the space for this reason.
Great food and portions, the service is always quick and friendly! Highly recommend the thai iced tea and ka pow jae.

Good portions and nice ambiance.  Service was poor -- took my order, delivered food, but never checked to see if I needed anything.  I ordered pad Thai medium and it was sickly sweet.  Possibly the worst flavored pad Thai I've ever had, and I've eaten this meal in a LOT of different places.

Good Thai food, a convenient location, and a great atmosphere all make this a solid restaurant!  I got lost at an intersection and asked some strangers where this place was and a lady kindly led me to this somewhat discreet restaurant. The place was pretty busy with a few people outside, some people waiting for takeout, and many tables taken inside, so I was expecting a pretty good meal. The interior is very nice, decorated like an Asian fusion place but a few traditional Thai/SouthEast Asian elements that add a nice touch to the design.  I ordered beef pad-see-ew and thai iced tea. The ice tea was average, it could've been a little sweeter and stronger. I enjoyed my pad see ew, The noodles were nice and thick, the beef was good, they were a little skimpy on Chinese broccoli but generous with eggs and beef. They gave so much I didn't even finish my meal and I was mega-craving Thai!  I really enjoyed my meal and the atmosphere, and recommend this place if you want Thai in DC or if you want to relax with friends and eat a place that's not too expensive.

Mai Thai is great for happy hour/dinner. It is never crowded, the food is standard (shrimp pad thai boasts big juicy shrimps... yum...) though a little on the pricier side, and there are lots of tropical cocktails to choose from.  I like sitting in the recessed outdoor area, because you get the benefit of being outside, but not at the same level as the cars and pedestrians. It's almost as if you are eating in a little garden.

Compared to the Mai Thai in Georgetown, this location is pretty much the same, but the tofu pad thai is just a tad not as good as the Georgetown location.  The pepper steak at this location is just as good as it normally is, and they also make good cocktails here as well.  Oh, and they also had oddly-shaped silverware at this location... it felt very awkward in my hand; first place I think I have ever commented on the silverware.

Given that I usually go to the Mai Thai location in Georgetown, I was pretty disappointed after my recent experience at this Mai Thai location. I ordered the exact same dish that I always get (tofu pad thai), but it was definitely not as delicious as I'm used to. The noodles were different somehow, and there was no egg in it. There was also less tofu, and it wasn't as yummy. And, I was a given a lemon wedge to squeeze over the top instead of a lime, which probably didn't help. Not to the mention the terribly awkwardly-shaped and heavy forks they had, which made my hand hurt. I would probably not visit this location again.
My work loves to go here. I have had the avocado salad twice.

Mai Thai is an extremely solid Thai restaurant. In fact, it used to be my favorite. It has great, modern decor, a wonderful drink selection, and a central location that made it easy to ask friends to gather there. And their dishes tend to be very good -- love their papaya salad and curries. That said, prices on all dishes have gone up by ~$2 in the past couple of years, and I've been disappointed at their tendency to take away certain ingredients. My favorite, the pineapple red curry, is now only red curry (last time I was there, the waiter told me he could add some pineapple for yet another $2). That said, I'd still recommend this place to anyone craving thai in the Dupont area.

This is one of the worst restaurants i have ever been to in DC. My girlfriend and i actually stopped by taco bell on new york ave after we were done eating at this fancy dump. First off the portions are so horribly small. For the portions to be so small, they should defintly step up their food quality. Their muscles are under-cooked, the curry-duck was more of a pineapple-soup with maybe 5 small pieces of duck the size of a nickle. My gf ordered the bankock sea breeze which was a seafood dish. The plate only consisted of 2 small shrimp, 2 scallops, half of 1 softshell-crab served on top of a bunch(and i mean a bunch) of cheap vegetables, with a cup full of rice. Far from what was advertised on the menu. I cannot eat at a restaurant that goes out of their way to portion out your food and still gives u poor quality. and to think we waited almost 45mins for our meal just to get served this crap.. I've had chinese takeout that was better than the crap that i was served at this place last night. PLEASE stay away from this restaurant as there are plenty of other nice restaurants in this area. If i can stop 1 person from going to this dump, i can feel better about my 130 dollar tab
Food was not bad, I ordered eggplant, but the patio was the best part.
The food here is impeccable! Need to come for Happy Hour to give a full review, but our office does birthday lunches here somewhat regularly and they have yet to disappoint.

I have no idea where all these good reviews come from. If I could give 0 stars to this restaurant I would, but because it's impossible it's 1. We had lunch on Saturday and it was the WORST tasting Thai food we ever ate. The "dumplings" looked and tasted like bad case of frozen Sui Mai not even heated trough in the microwave (the skins were extremely hot and the filling was still cold). YUK!!!..  The red curry was too watery, not spicy at all and tasteless as can be (probably reheated in microwave too from previous day leftovers). The Duck salad was over salted to the point of uneatable so we stooped eating it after first couple of bites. The service was not much better then the food. After sitting alone in the whole empty restaurant for 10 minutes we had to look for a  waiter to get a check. BTW all of this YUKKY food and service came to about $30 which doesn't look like a good value to us at all, so there is no question we are not returning and not recommending this place to anyone.
